article.description: Gabby Green had a triple-double, Kristine Anigwe scored 30 points and Mikayla Cowling added 29 in No. 19 California's 106-44 win over Cal-State Northridge on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Green's triple-double leads No. 19 Cal women
article.linkText: Green's triple-double leads No. 19 Cal women
article.story:
BERKELEY, Calif. --  Gabby Green had a triple-double, Kristine Anigwe scored 30 points and Mikayla Cowling added 29 in No. 19 California's 106-44 win over Cal-State Northridge on Wednesday night.

Green finished with 11 points, a career-best 14 assists and 10 rebounds for the Bears (9-2), whose 62-point margin was three shy of the program record.

Cal scored at least 106 for the third time during its four-game winning streak.

Cowling was 13 of 16 from the field, including 3 of 4 from 3-point range, and Anigwe was 13-of-17 shooting. Cal shot 45 of 66 overall (68.2 percent) and 8 of 10 from 3-point range.

Courtney Range added 12 points and Asha Thomas handed out 11 assists.

Jasmine Johnson led CS Northridge (2-11) with 14 points and seven rebounds. Serafina Maulupe scored 13 and Tessa Boagni added 10 points.

The Matadors lost their third in a row.
